WEBVTT

00:03.125 --> 00:04.392
You ever feel
self-conscious,

00:04.426 --> 00:06.427
Telling people that you work
at a comic book store?

00:06.462 --> 00:09.514
Whew, I still do at times,
you know?

00:09.548 --> 00:12.233
You meet captains of industry
out there.

00:12.268 --> 00:13.918
They ask, you know,
"what do you do for a living?"

00:13.953 --> 00:15.236
You gotta tell them you work
at a comic book store?

00:15.271 --> 00:16.721
Yeah, but you get
to tell people

00:16.772 --> 00:19.607
At least,
"I manage a comic book store,"

00:19.642 --> 00:22.010
Whereas I tell people,
"I work under a guy,"

00:22.044 --> 00:25.646
And they're like, "there are
two guys who actually do this?"

00:25.664 --> 00:26.948
But did you
even realize

00:26.982 --> 00:29.183
That you should've been
this self-conscious

00:29.218 --> 00:30.451
- About your position?
- Yeah, seriously.

00:30.486 --> 00:33.221
No, but, I mean,
I would've felt like--hey!

00:33.255 --> 00:34.789
At least I have a job.

00:34.823 --> 00:36.991
What makes you think
I don't have a job?

00:37.026 --> 00:38.927
The fact that you live
in your mom's basement.

00:38.961 --> 00:41.095
- You really think I live there?
- Yes.

00:41.130 --> 00:42.697
- Well, I do, but...
- [laughter]

00:42.731 --> 00:45.833
I got things going on,
irons in the fire.

00:45.868 --> 00:48.403
You know, the business
of being a free spirit.

00:48.437 --> 00:49.470
You're on the dole.

00:49.505 --> 00:51.539
The dole.

00:51.557 --> 00:52.640
[laughter]

00:52.675 --> 00:55.560
That's an interesting term.

00:55.594 --> 00:56.678
I haven't heard it
since this morning

00:56.712 --> 00:59.714
When my mom screamed at me
when I left.

00:59.748 --> 01:02.717
[exciting music]

