Hello, and welcome to another
episode of Comic Book Men,

01:37.636 --> 01:39.921
The only show that has the sack
to tell you

01:39.955 --> 01:42.690
That your crap
is worthless, man.

01:42.725 --> 01:43.958
I'm your host
Kevin Smith.

01:43.993 --> 01:45.593
- Bryan Johnson.
- Walt Flanagan.

01:45.628 --> 01:47.028
- Mike Zapcic.
- Ming Chen.

01:47.062 --> 01:48.029
Okay.

01:48.063 --> 01:49.597
Were there
any big-ticket items

01:49.615 --> 01:50.898
Coming through the door
this week?

01:50.933 --> 01:54.268
Biggest ticket
and maybe biggest bulk item

01:54.303 --> 01:57.872
Was something
that generated hours of fun,

01:57.906 --> 02:00.975
Tons of commerce
and quarters--

02:01.010 --> 02:02.610
Oh!

02:02.645 --> 02:04.045
- Hey, how are you?
- How you doing?

02:04.063 --> 02:05.980
I've got something
you may be interested in.

02:06.015 --> 02:07.148
What's that?

02:07.182 --> 02:08.483
Oh, you want to come outside
and take a look?

02:08.517 --> 02:09.866
- It's in the truck.
- You want to come with me?

02:09.918 --> 02:11.085
This kind of sounds
a little weird.

02:11.120 --> 02:12.220
Is there candy inside?

02:12.254 --> 02:13.671
'cause I'm willing
to take a risk.

02:13.722 --> 02:15.456
- [laughs]
- Why not?

02:15.491 --> 02:17.709
- Watch the store.
- Are you ready for this?

02:17.743 --> 02:20.762
- I guess so.
- Okay.

02:21.964 --> 02:23.631
Oh, no way!

02:23.666 --> 02:26.434
An original Asteroids
from 1979.

02:26.468 --> 02:32.940
[spaceship shooting,
explosions]

02:32.975 --> 02:34.425
I haven't seen one of them
in years.

02:34.460 --> 02:35.543
It's in good shape.

02:35.577 --> 02:37.478
- Ready to play.
- Where did you get it?

02:37.513 --> 02:39.380
I picked this machine
out of a hoarder's house.

02:39.415 --> 02:40.932
A hoarder's house?

02:40.966 --> 02:42.383
It sat in his second bedroom
for 30 years.

02:42.418 --> 02:45.186
It took us almost two hours
just to find it.

02:45.220 --> 02:48.322
Wow, you're trying to sell it
at a comic book store, huh?

02:48.357 --> 02:50.341
Well, I figured you guys gotta
do something in your spare time.

02:50.376 --> 02:52.293
- Fair enough.
- You want to see it work?

02:52.327 --> 02:54.362
- I'll bring it right inside.
- Awesome, man.

02:54.396 --> 02:57.732
My favorite Asteroids machine
in the world is the one

02:57.766 --> 02:59.417
At the Highlands
Recreation Center

02:59.451 --> 03:00.568
Because of Jason Mewes.

03:00.602 --> 03:02.603
So I was reading comics
one day,

03:02.638 --> 03:04.172
So was Walter,
door kicks open.

03:04.206 --> 03:06.741
Jason Mewes marches in.

03:06.775 --> 03:08.292
He immediate proceeds

03:08.343 --> 03:11.012
To fellate anything
somewhat phallic

03:11.046 --> 03:13.147
In the entire
recreation center.

03:13.182 --> 03:15.049
Me and Walter look up
from our comics,

03:15.084 --> 03:17.285
And we're watching him go
from thing to thing.

03:17.319 --> 03:19.821
Like, he grabs a flag pole,
he grabs a pool stick.

03:19.855 --> 03:21.822
Then he hit
the Asteroids machine,

03:21.840 --> 03:22.924
And as you know,
the Asteroids machine

03:22.958 --> 03:23.925
Doesn't have a joystick,

03:23.959 --> 03:26.027
It has buttons,
so he was sitting there,

03:26.061 --> 03:27.879
Looking at it, stymied,

03:27.930 --> 03:29.330
'cause there was nothing
to fellate.

03:29.348 --> 03:31.999
And instead, he was just like--
[rolls tongue]

03:32.017 --> 03:34.202
I said, "I want
to hang out with that kid."

03:34.236 --> 03:37.739
This machine changed the way
video games were made forever.

03:37.773 --> 03:41.242
It was before Pac-Man, it was
just before Space Invaders,

03:41.276 --> 03:43.194
And this thing had a line
going out the door.

03:43.245 --> 03:45.379
All right, well, what are you
looking to get for her?

03:45.397 --> 03:47.732
Well, I'm asking $1,100
for the machine.

03:47.766 --> 03:50.051
Ooh, $1,100, really?

03:50.085 --> 03:53.554
That's, like, 40,000 quarters.
[laughter]

03:53.589 --> 03:54.839
You're never going
to find another Asteroids

03:54.890 --> 03:57.291
In this type of condition
maybe in your lifetime.

03:57.326 --> 03:59.861
I don't know, man,
$1,100's a lot.

03:59.895 --> 04:00.878
Dude, come on,
it could be

04:00.929 --> 04:04.098
My christmas
and birthday present.

04:04.133 --> 04:05.967
You live and breathe
the nostalgia, I mean,

04:06.001 --> 04:09.320
What brings you back
to the late '70s more than this?

04:09.354 --> 04:12.573
I don't disagree, man,
but it's a bit pricey though.

04:12.608 --> 04:14.692
Would you take $500?

04:14.743 --> 04:15.910
I don't think
I'd go that low.

04:15.944 --> 04:17.245
Could you do $1,000?

04:17.279 --> 04:20.447
You do realize, like,
I could buy an app online

04:20.482 --> 04:21.983
For, like, for 99Â¢

04:22.017 --> 04:24.318
And play this and not have
a monstrosity of a machine

04:24.352 --> 04:26.037
Sitting in the middle
of my store though.

04:26.071 --> 04:27.288
It's not a monstrosity.

04:27.322 --> 04:29.891
It's a piece of art right here.
Look at that.

04:29.925 --> 04:31.809
You don't get that
with the app.

04:31.844 --> 04:34.812
You don't get the true heartbeat
with the app.

04:34.863 --> 04:37.315
$650.
That's the best I can do.

04:37.366 --> 04:39.667
I think the lowest I would
take for the unit is $900,

04:39.701 --> 04:41.819
And I may make you throw
in a t-shirt for that,

04:41.870 --> 04:43.337
But that's about as low
as I'm going.

04:43.372 --> 04:46.007
It's really a nice piece
of history.

04:46.041 --> 04:47.942
Excuse me,
are you going to buy that?

04:47.976 --> 04:49.143
Why?

04:49.161 --> 04:50.361
'cause I might be
interested in it.

04:50.412 --> 04:51.812
You want to make an offer
on this to Vince?

04:51.830 --> 04:53.080
Sure, yes.

04:53.115 --> 04:54.915
Would you be interested
in hearing an offer

04:54.933 --> 04:56.417
- From some guy off the street?
- Certainly.

04:56.435 --> 04:57.718
Certainly, I'm here
to sell this machine.

04:57.753 --> 04:59.253
All right,
being that you're

04:59.288 --> 05:00.888
In the stash now
and conducting business,

05:00.923 --> 05:02.490
I think it'd be fair,
you know,

05:02.524 --> 05:05.226
5% of the sale price
to the Stash.

05:05.260 --> 05:07.895
- That works for me.
- All right, what do you got?

05:07.930 --> 05:09.997
I know you wanted a t-shirt,
so I'll go $750,

05:10.031 --> 05:11.098
And I'll buy you
a t-shirt.

05:11.133 --> 05:12.867
Well, if I have to pay
a 5% commission,

05:12.901 --> 05:14.035
I'm going to have
to ask you to come up

05:14.069 --> 05:15.269
