08:21.915 --> 08:23.349
Best boots in the business
right there.

08:23.383 --> 08:25.751
Only a man can pull off
wearing work boots.

08:25.786 --> 08:27.053
Aw, but this one--

08:27.087 --> 08:30.656
Issue 300,
first Venom,

08:30.691 --> 08:33.226
And I definitely
would have an interest

08:33.260 --> 08:34.927
In the 9/11 issue
of Spider-Man.

08:34.962 --> 08:36.996
That's my favorite comic ever,
like, after I read it.

08:37.030 --> 08:39.198
Signed, John Romita Jr.

08:39.232 --> 08:42.784
To commemorate September 11th,
Marvel put out a comic book

08:42.818 --> 08:44.403
Written by
J. Michael Straczynski, I think.

08:44.438 --> 08:45.821
- Yes.
- A Spider-Man comic.

08:45.873 --> 08:47.273
Drawn by John Romita Jr.

08:47.307 --> 08:48.491
Ah, one of the best,

08:48.542 --> 08:50.293
The greatest Spider-Man artists
in the business.

08:50.327 --> 08:53.246
And it was a story of,
you know, look,

08:53.280 --> 08:55.781
Marvel's universe
is in Manhattan.

08:55.799 --> 08:57.466
It's in New York.
They don't make up names.

08:57.501 --> 09:00.052
They're a New-York-based
universe.

09:00.086 --> 09:02.471
So when September 11th
happened,

09:02.522 --> 09:03.723
You know, they felt like,

09:03.757 --> 09:05.091
"Look, we should comment.
We should do something."

09:05.125 --> 09:06.142
"We should acknowledge
that it happened

09:06.193 --> 09:07.526
In our universe too."

09:07.561 --> 09:09.729
Particularly because it's so--
when you think about,

09:09.763 --> 09:11.030
When you read comic books,

09:11.064 --> 09:12.765
There's always
some major villain

09:12.783 --> 09:14.567
Trying to do
something horrific

09:14.601 --> 09:16.569
To New York,
to some community.

09:16.603 --> 09:20.539
So here in real life,
something, like, ultra-horrific,

09:20.574 --> 09:23.376
So horrific it almost came
out of something fictional,

09:23.410 --> 09:26.111
Happened, and so they
decided to commemorate,

09:26.129 --> 09:27.246
Or at least acknowledge it.

09:27.281 --> 09:30.883
Very powerful issue,
very poignant.

09:30.901 --> 09:34.553
And, you know,
it really was, you know,

09:34.588 --> 09:37.456
Just, you know,
Spider-Man rocked to the core.

09:37.491 --> 09:39.792
You know,
he's very distraught, as,

09:39.826 --> 09:41.494
You know, as
any other new yorker would be,

09:41.528 --> 09:43.863
As anybody on the face
of the planet would be,

09:43.897 --> 09:46.198
Seeing such devastation
and horrific acts.

09:46.233 --> 09:48.117
They're all
in pretty solid shape.

09:48.168 --> 09:49.568
They look good.

09:49.603 --> 09:51.220
- But I just want these guys.
- Yeah, you just want those.

09:51.254 --> 09:52.471
- Not interested in those.
- All right.

09:52.506 --> 09:57.593
I'd like $500.

09:57.628 --> 10:00.880
[groans]

10:00.914 --> 10:03.916
Would you do $400?

10:03.934 --> 10:07.203
$475?

10:07.254 --> 10:09.055
$425?

10:09.089 --> 10:11.424
$455.

10:11.458 --> 10:14.093
$450, cash,
you got it.

